# Project Rules

## Tech Stack

- **Language**: Java 21 (LTS, virtual threads available)
- **Build Tool**: Maven 3.9+ with multi-module POM
- **Framework**: Spring Boot 3.2, Spring Cloud 2023.0
- **RabbitMQ**: Spring AMQP (`spring-boot-starter-amqp`, `RabbitTemplate`, `SimpleMessageListenerContainer`)
- **Vault**: Spring Cloud Vault (`spring-cloud-starter-vault-config`, `VaultTemplate`)
- **Circuit Breaker**: Resilience4j 2.2 (`resilience4j-spring-boot3`, `resilience4j-circuitbreaker`, `resilience4j-retry`)
- **Metrics**: Micrometer + Prometheus (`micrometer-registry-prometheus`)
- **Health**: Spring Boot Actuator (`spring-boot-starter-actuator`)
- **Logging**: SLF4J + Logback (`@Slf4j` from Lombok)
- **Validation**: Jakarta Bean Validation (`spring-boot-starter-validation`)
- **Lombok**: `@Data`, `@Slf4j`, `@Builder`, `@Value` annotations
- **Testing**: JUnit 5, Mockito, Testcontainers 1.19, AssertJ, spring-rabbit-test
- **Coverage**: JaCoCo 0.8.11

## Architecture

Multi-module Maven project. Three child modules under parent POM:

```
rabbitmq-client-java/           (parent POM: com.shoppingcart:rabbitmq-client-parent:1.0.0-SNAPSHOT)
├── rabbitmq-client/            (com.shoppingcart:rabbitmq-client) — core library JAR
│   └── src/main/java/com/shoppingcart/rabbitmq/
│       ├── RabbitMQClientAutoConfiguration.java  — Spring Boot auto-configuration entry point
│       ├── config/RabbitMQProperties.java        — @ConfigurationProperties(prefix="rabbitmq")
│       ├── connection/ConnectionManager.java     — AMQP ConnectionFactory management
│       ├── vault/VaultCredentialManager.java     — Spring Cloud Vault credential fetch/renewal
│       ├── vault/VaultCredentials.java           — Credential value object
│       ├── publisher/Publisher.java              — RabbitTemplate-based publisher, confirm mode
│       ├── publisher/PublishOptions.java         — Builder pattern, exchange/routingKey/headers
│       ├── publisher/BatchPublisher.java         — Batch publish with confirms
│       ├── consumer/Consumer.java                — SimpleMessageListenerContainer-based consumer
│       ├── consumer/ConsumeOptions.java          — Builder: queue, autoAck, prefetch, QueueOptions
│       ├── consumer/MessageHandler.java          — @FunctionalInterface for message callbacks
│       ├── retry/RetryConfig.java                — Resilience4j RetryRegistry from RabbitMQProperties
│       ├── circuitbreaker/CircuitBreakerConfig.java — Resilience4j CircuitBreakerRegistry
│       ├── metrics/RabbitMQMetrics.java          — Micrometer MeterRegistry wrappers
│       ├── health/RabbitMQHealthIndicator.java   — Spring Actuator HealthIndicator
│       ├── health/VaultHealthIndicator.java      — Spring Actuator HealthIndicator for Vault
│       ├── dlq/DLQManager.java                   — DLQ infrastructure setup
│       ├── dlq/DLQConfig.java                    — DLQ configuration record
│       ├── dlq/DLQMessage.java                   — Dead letter message wrapper
│       └── exception/                            — Typed exceptions (hierarchy)
├── rabbitmq-cli/               — Spring Boot app with PublisherCli + ConsumerCli
└── rabbitmq-examples/          — Spring Boot app with DemoExample, PublisherExample, ConsumerExample
```

Auto-configuration is registered via:
`rabbitmq-client/src/main/resources/META-INF/spring/org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.AutoConfiguration.imports`

## Code Conventions

- **Style**: Google Java Style Guide
- **Logging**: `@Slf4j` (Lombok); use `log.debug()`, `log.info()`, `log.warn()`, `log.error()` with `{}` placeholders; never use string concatenation in log calls
- **Null handling**: Use `Optional<T>` instead of returning null; use `@NonNull` where appropriate
- **DTOs / Value objects**: Prefer Java records or Lombok `@Value` for immutable objects
- **Local variables**: Use `var` when the type is obvious from the right-hand side
- **Builders**: Use Lombok `@Builder` on options/config classes; always implement `of()` static factory as convenience alias for `builder().build()` with required fields
- **Validation**: Annotate `@ConfigurationProperties` classes with `@Validated` and Jakarta Constraint annotations (`@NotBlank`, `@Min`, `@Max`)
- **Auto-configuration**: Use `@ConditionalOnMissingBean`, `@ConditionalOnBean`, `@ConditionalOnProperty` to make all beans overridable
- **Exception hierarchy**: All exceptions extend `RabbitMQException` (RuntimeException); `ConnectionException`, `PublishException`, `ConsumeException`, `CircuitBreakerOpenException`
- **Commit messages**: Conventional commits format: `type(scope): subject` — types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `test`, `refactor`, `perf`, `chore`

## Testing

Test class naming: `*Test` for unit, `*IT` for integration (Failsafe picks up `*IT`).
Surefire excludes `*IT.java` and `*IntegrationTest.java`.

```bash
make test            # unit tests (mvn test -pl rabbitmq-client -DskipITs)
make test-int        # integration tests with Docker (mvn verify -Pintegration)
make test-all        # all tests
make coverage        # JaCoCo report -> rabbitmq-client/target/site/jacoco/index.html
mvn test -Dtest=PublishOptionsTest          # single class
mvn test -Dtest=PublishOptionsTest#testBuilderDefaults  # single method
mvn test -Dtest="*OptionsTest"              # pattern match
```

Unit test patterns:
- Extend nothing; use `@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)` for Mockito
- Use `@Mock` / `@InjectMocks`; never `new` the class under test directly when it has dependencies
- Use AssertJ: `assertThat(x).isEqualTo(y)`, `assertThatThrownBy(() -> ...).isInstanceOf(...)`
- Follow Given/When/Then structure with comments
- Test method names: `should<Behavior>_when<Condition>()` pattern

Integration test patterns:
- Use `@Testcontainers` + `@Container` static fields
- `@DynamicPropertySource` to inject container ports into Spring context
- Use unique queue names per test: `"test-queue-" + System.currentTimeMillis()`
- Always `@DirtiesContext` if Spring context state is mutated

## Build & Run

```bash
# Build
make build       # mvn compile
make package     # mvn package -DskipTests
make install     # mvn install -DskipTests
make full-build  # mvn verify (with tests)

# Run Demo (recommended — single command, no setup)
make demo        # Spring Boot: DemoExample with demo profile (port 30672, demo/demo, no Vault)

# Run Examples separately
make run-publisher  # PublisherExample standalone
make run-consumer   # ConsumerExample standalone (waits indefinitely)

# CLI Tools
make cli-demo    # publish + consume in sequence (note: known issue, see below)
make cli-consume [QUEUE=name] [EXCHANGE=name]
make cli-publish [EVENT=type] [PAYLOAD=json] [COUNT=n]

# Dev Environment (Docker)
make dev-setup   # start containers + configure Vault
make dev-start   # docker compose up -d (RabbitMQ + Vault)
make dev-stop    # docker compose down
make dev-logs    # docker compose logs -f

# Code Quality
make lint        # checkstyle + spotbugs
make format      # spotless:apply
make format-check
make docs        # javadoc:aggregate

# Utility
make deps        # dependency tree
make deps-updates  # check for updates
```

Override connection settings:
```bash
RABBITMQ_HOST=localhost RABBITMQ_PORT=5672 RABBITMQ_USERNAME=guest RABBITMQ_PASSWORD=guest make demo
```

Demo profile config (`application-demo.yml`): port=30672, credentials=demo/demo, vault.enabled=false, circuit-breaker.enabled=false.

## Key Patterns

### Auto-Configuration
`RabbitMQClientAutoConfiguration` registers all beans. `ConnectionManager` has two variants: one that takes `VaultCredentialManager` (when Vault enabled) and one for static credentials (when `rabbitmq.vault.enabled=false`). All beans use `@ConditionalOnMissingBean` so consumers can override any component.

### Configuration Properties
`RabbitMQProperties` uses `@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "rabbitmq")` with nested static inner classes: `Pool`, `Retry`, `CircuitBreaker`, `Vault`. Lombok `@Data` generates getters/setters. `@Validated` + Jakarta annotations enforce constraints at startup.

### Publisher
`Publisher` wraps `RabbitTemplate`. Confirm mode via `rabbitTemplate.invoke()` + `waitForConfirms()`. Returns callback set for `setReturnsCallback()` to log unroutable messages. Body serialized via `ObjectMapper` (JSON) unless already `byte[]` or `String`.

### Consumer
`Consumer` creates and manages `SimpleMessageListenerContainer` instances keyed by consumer ID. Manual ack via `ChannelAwareMessageListener`; calls `channel.basicAck()` on success and `channel.basicNack()` on failure. `stopAll()` destroys all containers.

### Metrics
`RabbitMQMetrics` wraps `MeterRegistry`. `trackPublish()` / `trackConsume()` return `Runnable` completions (same deferred-function pattern as Go/Python siblings). `recordPublishError()` / `recordConsumeError()` increment error counters.

### Known Issue: CLI Tools
`PublisherCli` and `ConsumerCli` both implement `CommandLineRunner`. When packaged in the same JAR, Spring Boot runs both with the same args. Workaround: use `make demo` (DemoExample) instead of `make cli-demo`.
